('32884', '2', 'Place beans into a large saucepan of boiling water. cook 4 minutes.'),
('32884', '3', 'Drain and rinse with cold water. drain well.'),
('32884', '4', 'Place beans in a large bowl. set aside.'),
('32884', '5', 'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('32884', '6', 'Add oil to pan. swirl to coat.'),
('32884', '7', 'Add onion and thyme to pan. saut 4 minutes or until onion is tender, stirring occasionally.'),
('32884', '8', 'Add mushrooms. saut 10 minutes or until liquid almost evaporates, stirring frequently. Stir in wine, salt, and pepper. cook 2 minutes or until liquid almost evaporates. Stir in flour. cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually stir in chicken broth. bring to a boil. Cook 1 minute or until thick, stirring constantly.'),
('32884', '9', 'Add mushroom mixture to green beans. toss well.'),
('32884', '10', 'Place green bean mixture in a 2-quart glass or ceramic baking dish.'),
('32884', '11', 'Combine fried onions and grated cheese in a small bowl. Top green bean mixture evenly with fried onion mixture.'),
('32884', '12', 'Bake at 425 for 17 minutes or until top is lightly browned.'),
('32886', '1', 'Saute bacon strips in heavy large skillet over medium heat until brown and crisp. Using slotted spoon, transfer bacon to paper towels to drain. Reserve skillet and drippings.'),
('32886', '2', 'Cook beans in large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('32886', '3', 'Drain. transfer to large bowl. Cover bowl loosely with foil.'),
('32886', '4', 'Heat drippings in reserved skillet over medium heat. Sprinkle scallops with salt and pepper. Working in batches, add scallops to skillet. cook until browned, about 2 minutes per side.'),
('32886', '5', 'Transfer to bowl with beans. cover loosely with foil. Reserve skillet.'),
('32886', '6', 'Whisk vinegar, water, and mustard into drippings in reserved skillet. Boil over high heat until reduced by half, stirring frequently and scraping up browned bits, about 7 minutes. Stir in whipping cream. bring sauce to boil. Season to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('32886', '7', 'Add bacon to bowl with beans and scallops. mix gently. Divide mixture among 6 plates.'),
('32886', '8', 'Drizzle with sauce, sprinkle with dill, and serve.'),
('32888', '1', 'Cook beans in a large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, 4 to 6 minutes.'),
('32888', '2', 'Drain beans and toss with butter, zest, and salt to taste.'),
('32892', '1', 'Preheat oven to 42'),
('32892', '2', 'Place beans into a large saucepan of boiling water. cook 4 minutes.'),
('32892', '3', 'Drain and rinse with cold water. drain well.'),
('32892', '4', 'Place beans in a large bowl. set aside.'),
('32892', '5', 'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('32892', '6', 'Add oil to pan. swirl to coat.'),
('32892', '7', 'Add onion and thyme to pan. saut 4 minutes or until onion is tender, stirring occasionally.'),
('32892', '8', 'Add mushrooms. saut 10 minutes or until liquid almost evaporates, stirring frequently. Stir in wine, salt, and pepper. cook 2 minutes or until liquid almost evaporates. Stir in flour. cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually stir in chicken broth. bring to a boil. Cook 1 minute or until thick, stirring constantly.'),
('32892', '9', 'Add mushroom mixture to green beans. toss well.'),
('32892', '10', 'Place green bean mixture in a 2-quart glass or ceramic baking dish.'),
('32892', '11', 'Combine fried onions and grated cheese in a small bowl. Top green bean mixture evenly with fried onion mixture.'),
('32892', '12', 'Bake at 425 for 17 minutes or until top is lightly browned.'),
('32898', '1', 'Place beans in a large pot of boiling salted water and cook until tender, about 8 minutes.'),
('32898', '2', 'Drain and rinse under cold water.'),
('32898', '3', 'In a large skillet, warm butter over medium-high heat until golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('32898', '4', 'Add pecans and cook, stirring, until lightly toasted, 2 minutes.'),
('32898', '5', 'Add beans, season with salt and pepper and cook, stirring, until heated through, 2 minutes.'),
('32898', '6', 'Transfer to a serving platter.'),
('32898', '7', 'Serve hot.'),
('32900', '1', 'Stir together corn, beans, soup, sour cream and cheese. spread in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs. drizzle with melted butter.'),
('32900', '2', 'Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for one hour or until golden.'),
('32905', '1', 'Bring a large pot of water to boil, add the green beans, cook until they just start to turn tender and plunge then them into cold water.Melt the butter in a pan over medium heat.'),
('32905', '2', 'Add the onions and cook until tender, about 5-7 minutes.'),
('32905', '3', 'Add the mushrooms and saute until the mushrooms start to caramelize, about 10-15 minutes.'),
('32905', '4', 'Add the garlic and thyme and saute until fragrant, about a minute.Sprinkle then mix the flour in and cook for another 2 minutes.'),
('32905', '5', 'Add the white wine and deglaze the pan.'),
('32905', '6', 'Add the broth and cream and simmer until it thickened, about 2-3 minutes.'),
('32905', '7', 'Add the cheese and let it melt, season with salt and pepper and remove from heat.'),
('32905', '8', 'Mix the green beans into the mushroom sauce and pour into a baking dish.'),
('32905', '9', 'Mix the melted butter, bread crumbs and french fried onions and sprinkle onto the casserole.'),
('32905', '10', 'Bake in a preheated 400F oven until the sides are bubbling and the top is golden brown, about 10-15 minutes.'),
('32907', '1', 'Preheat oven to 40'),
('32907', '2', 'Cut onions in half vertically.'),
('32907', '3', 'Drizzle the cut side of each onion half with 1/4 teaspoon oil. Sprinkle halves evenly with salt and pepper.'),
('32907', '4', 'Place 1 thyme sprig on 1 onion half. top with other half. Wrap in foil. Repeat procedure with the remaining thyme and onion halves.'),
('32907', '5', 'Bake the wrapped onions at 400 for 1 hour or until tender. Cool to room temperature. Discard thyme, and chop onions.'),
('32907', '6', 'Combine 1 tablespoon olive oil, onion, dill, vinegar, and mustard in a small bowl.'),
('32907', '7', 'Toss the beans with the vinaigrette.'),
('32909', '1', 'Heat 2 inches oil in a 4-quart heavy pot over moderate heat until a deep-fat thermometer registers 365F.'),
('32909', '2', 'While oil is heating, make dipping sauce by stirring together soy sauce, lime juice, and sugar until sugar is dissolved. 3'),
('32909', '3', 'Whisk together flour and sesame seeds and whisk in beer until batter is smooth.'),
('32909', '4', 'Toss about 10 beans in batter until coated.'),
('32909', '5', 'Add to oil 1 at a time (to keep separate) and fry, turning, until golden, about 1 1/2 minutes.'),
('32909', '6', 'Transfer with tongs to paper towels to drain and sprinkle with salt to taste. Coat and fry remaining beans in same manner.'),
('32909', '7', 'Serve beans with dipping sauce.'),
('32910', '1', 'In a microwave safe bowl, add green beans and 1 tablespoon water. Cover with plastic wrap and cook on high setting for 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.'),
('32910', '2', 'While green beans are cooking. in a large frying pan, heat the butter, oil, sliced garlic, and chopped bacon gently over medium heat. NOTE: Do not let garlic burn - a light golden brown is as dark as garlic should get.'),
('32910', '3', 'Drain any liquid from the green beans and add to frying pan. Toss to coat beans and season with salt and pepper.'),
('32911', '1', 'Steam beans, covered, 7 minutes or until crisp-tender.'),
('32911', '2', 'Drain and return to pan.'),
('32911', '3', 'Add parsley and remaining ingredients. toss gently to combine.'),
('32911', '4', 'Serve immediately.'),
('32914', '1', 'Cook beans in a 6- to 8-quart pot of boiling salted water, uncovered, until crisp-tender, 4 to 5 minutes.'),
('32914', '2', 'Drain in a colander and immediately transfer to a bowl of ice and cold water to stop cooking. When beans are cool, drain and pat dry.'),
('32914', '3', 'Whisk together oils, vinegar, mustard, salt, and pepper in a large bowl until combined well, then add beans and sesame seeds and toss to coat.'),
('32918', '1', 'Stir together onion, vinegar, mustard, 3/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in a large bowl. Marinate about 10 minutes.'),
('32918', '2', 'Meanwhile, cook beans in a large pot of well-salted boiling water, uncovered, until just tender, about 6 minutes.'),
('32918', '3', 'Transfer to a large ice bath to stop cooking.'),
('32918', '4', 'Drain and pat dry.'),
('32918', '5', 'Whisk oil and parsley into onion mixture, then toss with beans.'),
('32920', '1', 'Finely chop or grate eggs. Spoon them over green beans that have been tossed with a prepared or homemade balsamic vinaigrette. Top with chopped fresh tarragon and chopped kalamata olives.'),
('32922', '1', 'To medium Dutch oven, add 2 cups canola oil and heat to 350 degrees F.'),
('32922', '2', 'In medium saute pan over medium heat, add 1 tablespoon oil.'),
('32922', '3', 'Add ginger and saute for 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('32922', '4', 'Add garlic and cook for 1 minute or until it turns light brown. quickly add soy sauce, chili sauce, rice wine vinegar, hoisin, mirin, sesame oil and cilantro.'),
('32922', '5', 'Fry the green beans in the canola oil for about 45 seconds, or until beans turn dark green.'),
('32922', '6', 'Remove, strain, and add to sauce. Toss and garnish with peanuts and parsley.'),
('32927', '1', 'Preheat oven to 35'),
('32927', '2', 'Bake almonds in a single layer in a shallow pan 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly toasted and fragrant, stirring halfway through.'),
('32927', '3', 'Cook green beans in boiling salted water to cover 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender. drain. Plunge beans into ice water to stop the cooking process. drain.'),
('32927', '4', 'Whisk together vinegar and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl. add olive oil in a slow, steady stream, whisking constantly until blended and smooth.'),
('32927', '5', 'Add cherry tomatoes, shallots, garlic, and green beans. toss to coat.'),
('32927', '6', 'Top green bean mixture with crumbled goat cheese and toasted almonds.'),
('32927', '7', '*White wine vinegar may be substituted.'),
('32930', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 35'),
('32930', '2', 'Spread the pine nuts in a pie plate and bake for about 7 minutes, shaking the plate occasionally to prevent scorching, until the pine nuts are lightly toasted.'),
('32930', '3', 'Let cool.'),
('32930', '4', 'In a pot of boiling, salted water, cook the beans until just tender, about 4 minutes.'),
('32930', '5', 'Drain in a colander and refresh under cold running water. drain well.'),
('32930', '6', 'In a large bowl, combine the pine nuts with the chopped basil, roasted red peppers and garlic.'),
('32930', '7', 'Add the olive oil and lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.'),
('32930', '8', 'Add the green beans and toss to mix.'),
('32930', '9', 'Garnish the beans with the basil leaves and serve.'),
('32932', '1', 'Combine vinegar and shallots in heavy small saucepan. Boil over medium heat until most vinegar is absorbed (about 1 tablespoon liquid should remain in pan), stirring frequently, about 6 minutes.'),
('32932', '2', 'Transfer mixture to small bowl. cool completely.'),
('32932', '3', 'Add butter. mix with fork until blended.'),
('32932', '4', 'Cook beans in large pot of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 6 minutes.'),
('32932', '5', 'Drain. Refresh under cold water. drain. Pat dry with paper towels. (Balsamic-shallot butter and beans can be made 1 day ahead. Cover separately. chill.)'),
('32932', '6', 'Combine beans and balsamic-shallot butter in large nonstick skillet. Toss over medium heat until beans are heated through, about 5 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve.'),
('32935', '1', 'Arrange green beans in a steamer basket over boiling water. Cover and steam 5 to 7 minutes. Plunge into ice water to stop the cooking process. drain.'),
('32935', '2', 'Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. add shallots, and saut 3 minutes or until tender.'),
('32935', '3', 'Add green beans, tomato, and next 3 ingredients. Cook 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.'),
('32935', '4', 'Serve immediately.'),
('32941', '1', 'In a large saucepan of lightly salted boiling water, cook the green beans uncovered for 7 to 9 minutes or until tender.'),
('32941', '2', 'Drain and rinse in cold water. In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, vinegar, mustard, and salt.'),
('32941', '3', 'Pour the dressing over the green beans and toss well. Fold in the tomatoes and goat cheese, then add pepper to taste.'),
('32941', '4', 'To make up to 2 days ahead, prepare and store separately in the refrigerator: green beans, dressing, tomatoes, and cheese.'),
('32941', '5', 'Combine up to 3 hours before serving.'),
('32951', '1', 'To prepare vinaigrette, combine first 7 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring with a whisk.'),
('32951', '2', 'To prepare beans, cook beans in a large pot of boiling water 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.'),
('32951', '3', 'Drain well.'),
('32951', '4', 'Place beans in a large bowl.'),
('32951', '5', 'Add lemon mixture. toss well to coat. Sprinkle with almonds and thyme.'),
('32952', '1', 'Cook the pasta according to the package directions. Meanwhile, place the potatoes and salt in a large saucepan.'),
('32952', '2', 'Add enough cold water to cover. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until the potatoes are almost but not quite tender, about 15 minutes.'),
